y, lexicography and international language organisation; linguistic change and varieties; language management and the social sciences; French and national languages. This extremely wide-ranging collection also points up various socio-linguistic constellations and language management in a number of very different regions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguage planning. 0aLanguage policy. 0aLanguages in contact. 0aSociolinguistics. 4aCorbeil, Jean-Claude. 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aSprachkontakt. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aArchambault, Ariane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuger, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasque, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastardas-Boada, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeauchemin, Normand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertrand, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBessé, Brano de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBibeau, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBnoussina, Khadija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoudreau, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoufarra, Abdelkrim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoulanger, Jean-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBourhis, Richard Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCajolet-Laganière, Hélène, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastellví, Teresa Ca